      <subsection name="Examples" id="ParameterNumber_Examples">
        <p>
          To configure the check:
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name="ParameterNumber"/&gt;
        </source>

        <p>
          To configure the check to allow 10 parameters for a method:
        </p>
        <source>
&lt;module name="ParameterNumber"&gt;
  &lt;property name="max" value="10"/&gt;
  &lt;property name="tokens" value="METHOD_DEF"/&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
        </source>
          <p>
              To configure the check to ignore number of parameters for methods with @Override
              or @java.lang.Override annotation.
          </p>
          <p>
              Rationale: developer may need to override method with many parameters from
              3-rd party library.
              In this case developer has no control over number of parameters.
          </p>
          <source>
&lt;module name="ParameterNumber"&gt;
  &lt;property name="ignoreOverriddenMethods" value="true"/&gt;
  &lt;property name="tokens" value="METHOD_DEF"/&gt;
&lt;/module&gt;
          </source>
          <p>
              Java code example
          </p>
          <source>
@Override
public void needsLotsOfParameters(int a, int b, int c, int d, int e, int f, int g, int h) {
    ...
}
          </source>
